# promoter_db.fasta — reference promoter/origin sequences for vector screening
#
# Sources:
#   - Canonical SV40 entries: NC_001669.1 (reference strain 776)
#   - pCMV-BD backbone variants: extracted from OR134577.1_genbank.gb
#     (Pfizer BNT162b2 vector), which comprehensive_vector_analysis.json
#     confirmed shares 100% identity with pCMV-BD AF151088.1 at these
#     positions. See VECTOR_CORRECTED_VERDICT_20260712.txt for the
#     chain of evidence.
#
# Why both canonical and pCMV-BD variants are present:
#   The Pfizer/Moderna vaccines use pCMV-family backbones, not canonical
#   SV40. Single-base mismatches between the two caused false negatives
#   in vaccine_vector_screen.py at 90% identity thresholds. Including
#   both variants lets probes match either backbone.
#
# CHANGELOG:
#   2026-07-13: Removed broken SV40_origin placeholder (was GATCGATCGATCGATCGATC).
#               Added pCMV-BD_SV40_early_polyA, pCMV-BD_f1_origin,
#               pCMV-BD_SV40_early_promoter_ori.

>SV40_early  source=NC_001669.1  note=canonical_sv40_reference
GAGGCAGAGGCGGGGGCGGAGCCGGGGGCGGGGGCTGAGGGGGCGGGAGGAGGGCGGGAGGGGGCTGAGGGCGGAGGGCGGAGGGGGCGGG

>SV40_late  source=NC_001669.1  note=canonical_sv40_reference
